      "id": "770e8400-e29b-41d4-a716-446655440900",
      "title": "Appendix: Test Evidence Templates",
      "level": 1,
      "description": "Templates for capturing test evidence",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "770e8400-e29b-41d4-a716-446655440901",
          "type": "STATIC_TEXT",
          "title": "Evidence Documentation Requirements",
          "staticText": "## Required Test Evidence\n\nFor each test executed, the following evidence must be captured and retained:\n\n### 1. Test Execution Log\n- Test ID and description\n- Execution date and time\n- Tester name\n- Environment details\n- Input data used\n- Actual results obtained\n- Pass/Fail determination\n- Screenshots or output files\n\n### 2. Defect Documentation\n- Defect ID and title\n- Steps to reproduce\n- Expected vs. actual behavior\n- Severity and priority\n- Screenshots/logs\n- Resolution details\n\n### 3. Sign-off Documentation\n- Test summary report\n- Defect metrics\n- Coverage analysis\n- Approval signatures\n\n### 4. Retention Requirements\n- All test evidence must be retained for a minimum of 7 years\n- Evidence should be stored in the designated document repository\n- Evidence must be version controlled and access restricted",
          "regenerationPolicy": {"allowed": false, "maxAttempts": 1, "cacheKeyStrategy": "none"},
          "citationPolicy": {"requireCitations": false, "allowedSources": []}
        }
